t1314.text: In the US, Disneyland has shut, sporting events have been called off and flights to Europe have been cancelled. IMHO we should be doing the same to stop the virus spreading. It will hurt the economy, but it will be worse in the long run if we don’t act.

t1315.text: Children are seemingly being spared, but as a mum of a toddler, I can’t help worrying. It makes me nervous that we’re relying on people “doing the right thing” in Australia. I think we need to be more proactive.

t1316.text: I’m no longer laughing about coronavirus. I’m increasingly concerned about the older and elderly people in my life (and those I don’t know). I lost my dad this time last year, so the loss of more people close to me feels very real. (1/4)
